comment: RATR shows that Fournier (ORL) cleanly strips the ball from Knight (PHO).
Orlando never gains possession prior to the 24 Second Violation by Phoenix. The shot clock was incorrectly reset for the ensuing jump ball.
Harris (ORL) makes contact with Bledsoe's (PHO) arm that affects his RSBQ on the drive to the basket.
Len (PHO) makes contact with Vucevic's (ORL) body that affects his driving shot attempt.
RATR shows that Oladipo (ORL) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Bledsoe's (PHO) drive to the basket and layup attempt.
Vucevic (ORL) firms up as he sets the screen on Booker (PHO) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Len (PHO) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Fournier's (ORL) drive and layup attempt.
Oladipo (ORL) makes incidental contact with Bledsoe (PHO) that does not affect his RSBQ at the start of the drive.
RHH shows that Oladipo (ORL) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Tucker (PHO) in the corner and legally contests his jump shot attempt.
Payton (ORL) gains possession in the frontcourt and then goes into the backcourt after losing control of the ball. A backcourt violation is correctly called.
Oladipo (ORL) commits a take foul on Bledsoe (PHO).
[Observable in enhanced video] Using freeze frame, Bledsoe (PHO), who is the FT shooter, enters the lane prior to the ball hitting the rim.
Vucevic (ORL) extends his leg as he sets the screen on Tucker (PHO) and does not give him room to avoid the contact.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the ball was touched simultaneously prior to going OOB was overturned. Orlando was awarded possession.
Vucevic (ORL) continues to move as he sets the screen on Bledsoe (PHO) without giving him room to avoid the contact.
Vucevic (ORL) sets the screen on Bledsoe (PHO) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the ball was last touched by Booker (PHO) was upheld. Orlando retained possession.
Len (PHO) maintains legal guarding position as Fournier (ORL) jumps to his right and initiates the contact with Len during his jump shot attempt.
